messages.content: ComfyUI_Substring is a simple custom node in ComfyUI that takes text and length as input and outputs the first length characters of the text.
ComfyUI_Substring takes two inputs: text and length.
ComfyUI_Substring outputs the first length characters of the input text.
To install ComfyUI_Substring, you need to git clone the repo in the \ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ directory.
Is ComfyUI_Substring a built-in node in ComfyUI?
No, ComfyUI_Substring is a custom node that needs to be installed separately, not a built-in node in ComfyUI.
Can ComfyUI_Substring take multiple input strings?
The documentation does not specify if ComfyUI_Substring can take multiple input strings. It only mentions that it takes text and length as input.
Is the length input in ComfyUI_Substring required?
Yes, the length input is required in ComfyUI_Substring, as it determines how many characters to output from the start of the input text.
